<h2 id="use-statements-for-core-php-classes">use Statements for core PHP Classes? <a class="headerlink" href="namespaces-core-php-classes#use-statements-for-core-php-classes" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Here, we see the <em>exact</em> same error as before: "Undefined Class <code>PDO</code>". So far, the
answer to this has always been:</p>
<blockquote><p>Oh, I must have forgotten a <code>use</code> statement. I referenced a class, so I probably
  need to add a <code>use</code> statement for it.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>But here's the kicker: <code>PDO</code> is a <em>core</em> PHP class that happens to <em>not</em> live in
a namespace. In other words, it's like a file that lives at the root of you file
system: not in any directory.</p>
<p>So when PHP sees <code>PDO</code> mentioned, it looks at the top of the class for a <code>use</code> statement
that ends in PDO, it doesn't find one, and it assumes that <code>PDO</code> lives in the <code>Service</code>
namespace. But in fact, <code>PDO</code> lives at the root namespace.</p>
<p>The fix is easy: add a <code>\</code> at the front of <code>PDO</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="ac92a76bf7">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
            <span class="fa fa-clipboard js-activate-clipboard" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Copy Code" data-placement="top"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="info">
                        <span class="js-expand-all" data-range="1-74" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Show All Lines" data-placement="top">
                <i class="fa fa-expand js-icon-load-more"></i>
                <i class="fa fa-spinner fa-spin js-icon-loading"></i>
            </span>
            
            74 lines <span class="meta-divider"></span> <span title="lib/Service/Container.php">lib/Service/Container.php</span>
        </div>
    </div>
    <table class="hljs code-block-table">
        <tbody class="js-tr-container">
                <tr>
                    <td class="line-number line-number-expandable" data-range="1-4" data-last="0">
                <i class="fa fa-arrows-v js-icon-load-more" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Show Lines" data-placement="left"></i>
                <i class="fa fa-spinner fa-spin js-icon-loading"></i>
            </td>
            <td class="gap-line">
